<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Solution: Get a High Powered Weapon</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Rainman">Rainman</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:24 a.m. 26/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Solution: Get a High Powered Weapon<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1724" TARGET=_self>Melee</A> (SD)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Well, I was in East Commons yesterday with my level 10 rogue. I

<BR>&gt; saw 4 level 5 dark elves killing humans so I went up and
<BR>&gt; attacked one of them who got left behind. I started swinging and
<BR>&gt; hitting for OK damage so, of course, he runs away. The big
<BR>&gt; problem with this is I have no way to catch him and it's hard as
<BR>&gt; hell to hit a moving target. Anyone can escape a melee character
<BR>&gt; but with magic users, all they have to do is target the person
<BR>&gt; and hit the button. This is ridiculous.
<P>&gt; Bottom line is, something needs to be done. Melee does hardly
<BR>&gt; any damage, and people can escape you anytime they want. The
<BR>&gt; only time a melee character will be able to kill someone solo is
<BR>&gt; if they're trying to kill him and lose agility due to injury.
<BR>&gt; Something needs to be done!!
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
